value.0: "Oh, hello there. If it isn't the nice, young hero. I sure wish I could vote in the election for you. Alas, it is not to be. So would you like to share a bit of gossip with a poor old woman?"
"Now, you come back and visit with your Momma Dane often."
"What kind of questions would you like to ask Momma Dane?"
"Was there any other gossip Momma Dane can share with such a sweet <boy/girl> as you?"
"I would love to chat with you about this home of ours. What questions do you have?"
"Oh, those horrid monsters! How dare they attack a nice keep like this? But I'm not worried. I'm sure you will take good care of us and slaughter those beasts in no time."
"You should really speak to Serah Blackhand. I'll bet she could find you a lovely home to purchase. She's such a dear."
"I personally would recommend Southpaw. He's a flatterer, but such a nice boy."
"I would go speak to The Stan, such a nice young half-orc. He has jobs for everyone. Well, except little old ladies with no skills of their own."
"Yeah, see? My friend has questions about the keep, so you better be answering them quick, see?"
"Oh my, what a frightening, young creature; and yet he's kind of cute, in a pestilence-spreading, bottom feeder sort of way."
"Trip likes her, <FirstName>. Can we keep her, please? Trip promises to feed her and take care of her and play with her everyday."
"Sorry, <FirstName>, Trip just got caught up in the excitement of this conversation."
"Oh, my poor old bones couldn't handle too much work. I had a little bit of gold from my dead husband, so I moved here to retire."
"It is a bit of a story, explaining why I moved here. But, probably you're not interested in a poor old woman's ramblings."
"Well, of course not. You have far more important things to worry about than me. You must have more important questions to ask me."
"If you are sure you're really interested. My husband was a demon hunter, which meant he lived on the road, traveling the world and looking for his prey."
"Temples would hire him, as would local governments who were being plagued by the demons. There always seemed to be plenty of the monsters for him to deal with."
"I often felt like a widow, with him being gone all the time. Then one day, one of the creatures managed to kill him and suddenly I really was a widow."
"My husband refused to take me with him when he traveled because of the danger. I am sure that if I had been with him, I could have done nothing to save his life."

"That still doesn't stop me from blaming myself. I picture him in my mind; the look of terror in his eyes, the scream that must have started to come from his lips as the demon tore his head from his neck."
"I always told him that he would come to a bad end, if he didn't change his ways."
"Yes, his life was given up in the service of a greater good."
"That is how they found his body... headless. It must have been a horrible way to go."
"But that is in the past, and I must try not to dwell on it. I was tired of living in comfort and wealth, yet constant loneliness, so I sold everything and traveled the world."
"Finally, I came to this keep. I loved the vibrancy of life here. There is always an element of danger, yet, because I do not fear death, I can live here and love life."

"Enough wasting your precious time. You must have more important things to do than hear me go on. Thank you for listening to me though. It is nice to bend an ear once in a while with personal stories."
"He was one of the most powerful men in the south, though he sought no fame. Despite my affluent lifestyle, it was a lonely existence."
"Oh yes, he left me a fair bit of gold. I lived very well, but it was a lonely existence."
"This seems like an unusual spot to retire. Would it not have been better to live in the civilized lands of the south?"
"There are nine guilds, each headed by a man or woman who has somehow convinced the other members of their guild that they can represent their needs."
"It would be easiest to break them into groups of how each guild master would vote, if you were not in the election."
"Enivid has her staunch supporters, Sir Becket has his and there are three who are relatively neutral."
"Yenna is the mage guild master, Serah is the landowners guild master, and LevioSa is the foresters guild master."
"Serah is a very earthy woman, and she is Alias's aunt. She has lands just outside of town and has been asking for help from the military guild for almost a year now."
"I am sure Alias could come up with some way for you to earn her vote. Treat Alias right, <FirstName>. She is young, but wise beyond her years."
"The Floating Huntress is the guildmaster of the Foresters. She was a ranger at one time, but now she has settled here at the keep and buys hides from the hunters and sells them supplies."
"Enivid made the mistake of insulting her and her fellow hunters, so you probably have a good chance of earning her trust. Anything else?"
"Yenna is the only powerful mage in town. She is also the only guildmaster with no other members of her guild."
"With her powers, no one really questions her, and she doesn't spend a lot of time with anyone unless she needs something for her research. I know little about her.  Anyone else?"
"Thaddeus is the merchant guild master, Southpaw is the thieves guild master, and Ellysia is the nobles guild master."
"She is the most popular noble. Rich, beautiful and so beyond the realities of this world she can't be bothered to see the problems we face."
"She is Sir Becket's acknowledged lover, so I see little chance of you changing her vote. Anyone else?"
"Although Southpaw is the guildmaster of the thieves, he is actually very well liked. I often enjoy his company during the day. He has an unusual sense of humor.
"I must confess; part of why I enjoy his company so much is that he flatters me relentlessly. Anyone else?"
"Thaddeus Squilt is the merchant guildmaster and a despicable person. He uses people, then destroys them."
"I wish Gelani was still guildmaster, but she lost the position to Thaddeus. He knew who to bribe and how to get more gold for the guild."
"If you're not afraid to get your hands a little dirty, you might be able to corrupt him, but don't trust him. Anyone else?"
"Oh, I forgot, Thaddeus is no longer the guildmaster. Gelani usurped his position and is voting for you now."
"Dynschall is the priests guild master, Feran is the military guild master, and The Stan is the trades guild master."
"Feran is an elf with a strict code of honor and I cannot think of a single way you could get him to vote for you. He owes everything to Enivid."
"You can usually find him in his office in the castle, though at night he does occasionally spend the evening at the Mossy Tree; a tavern and inn in here in the south keep. Anyone else?"
Momma Dane grins and chuckles softly. "The Stan is... unusual. He runs the trades office and if you are looking to make a little gold, he's the man to see."
"He believes in strong government and stability. If you do a job for him, do it right. Anybody else?"
"He is the head priest at the Temple of the Nine Gods. He nags me about not spending enough time communing with the gods, but I prefer people to gods."
"Just show him proper respect. He very much believes that the church must support the community. He also listens to his followers, so talk to them as well. Anyone else?"
"The nine guildmasters will meet in the castle, where they will each cast a stone; a different color for each of the contestants. The person with the most votes wins."
"You need at least four votes, with no other opponent getting more than three. That's about it. Not too difficult to understand, even for someone with an old mind like me.
"I know the one thing you are probably most interested in... the election. I keep my ears open and I can tell you how you stand with the guilds, or just tell you how things look, overall."
"I guess that is up to you. If I wanted to be the Lady of the Keep, I should care very much, but you will do things as you see fit. I just wanted to share the gossip."
"Right now, Enivid has <CUSTOM6001> votes; Sir Becket has <CUSTOM6002>; and you have <CUSTOM6003> votes."
"Are you sure you don't want to know who is voting for whom?"
"There are guild masters who are staunch supporters of Enivid, strong supporters of Sir Becket and some who tend to remain more neutral. Which group do you want specifics on?"
"What else would you like?"
"These ones pick sides, but they aren't particularly attached to one side or the other. They include the landowners guild, the mage guild and the foresters guild."
"Levio'Sa appears to have settled on voting for you, congratulations."
"Levio'Sa doesn't like either choice, but unless you prove yourself, she will end up siding with Sir Becket, just to spite Enivid."
"Yenna might be on your side, though I cannot be sure. We don't talk very much, since she spends most of her time in her tower."
"Yenna is a difficult one to read. I don't think it would take much to get her on your side, but if you don't try she'll probably end up voting for Enivid."
"Serah seems to have taken a liking to you. She supports you fully."
"Serah will probably side with Enivid, unless you can prove yourself to her."
"Those are the thieves guild, the merchant guild, and the nobles guild."
"I don't know how you did it, but Ellysia will be voting for you now."
"Ellysia stands solidly with her lover, Sir Becket. Good luck changing her mind."
"The merchants will now be voting for you, I am pleased to say."
"The merchants are firmly behind Sir Becket."
"Southpaw, the dear, is voting for you now. I am glad someone was able to steal him away from ugly Sir Becket."
"Southpaw is voting for Sir Becket."
"Those are the priests guild, the military guild and the trades guild."
"You must have impressed The Stan, because he has changed his vote to support you now."
"The Stan and his tradesmen still support Enivid."
"It is a very surprising turnabout, but now the military guild is voting for you. I am deeply impressed that you managed that."
"The military guild is still very much aligned with Enivid."
"Somehow you managed to sway Dynschall's opinion. The priest guild will vote for you."
"The priests guild still supports Enivid."
"Why, I am only Momma Dane. I just enjoy visiting with nice folk here in the keep. It really is a wonderful place, don't you think. It would be such a nice place to raise a family."
"But I am an old woman, far beyond my child rearing years. That's why I enjoy the young ones here so much. They almost make me forget the inevitable march of time."
"Now, no more melancholy thoughts. Let us find a more interesting subject to converse on. We should enjoy a little gossip, perhaps."
"What hope is there for a family to live in a place so close to the wilds? There is nothing but heartache and pain in such a place."
"It is the pain that makes us feel life with more vibrancy. Life can be harsh, it is true, but with time, the pain fades and others can come into our lives to make us feel whole again."
"Your words shame me. My mind needs to overcome the past, but I am not there yet."
"I would sooner raise a family outside the keep, where nature thrives. Though I fear I shall never have that opportunity."
"You are yet young, and no one knows what the future may hold for them. You still contain beauty, should you choose to look for it."
"Goodbye."
"I have other questions."
"That is all my questions."
"I have questions about the keep."
"That's all my questions about the keep."
"What do you know about the invaders?"
"Where can I get a room?"
"Where can I get equipment?"
"Where can I find employment?"
"Shut up, Trip!"
"I'm sure she will answer my questions with out a threat, Trip."
"What is wrong with you, Trip?"
"You had better do as he says. He sometimes loses control of himself."
"I can't take you anywhere, Trip!"
"Let it go, Trip."
"Just shut up, Trip!"
"What do you do here in the keep?"
"You're right. I don't really care."
"I can listen for a while."
"Please tell me."
"How did the demon kill him?"
"That's what you get for dealing with demons."
"Sounds like a bad end to a noble life."
"That is... very graphic."
"I like living on the edge of danger too."
"I'd prefer somewhere safer."
"I like the way you look at the world."
"That is a healthy attitude."
"Your husband must have been pretty powerful."
"Did he make a good living?"
"What can you tell me about the guildmasters?"
"I changed my mind."
"Tell me more."
"Who are the neutral guild masters?"
"Tell me about Serah."
"Tell me about Levio'Sa."
"Tell me about Yenna."
"Who are Sir Becket's supporters?"
"Tell me about Ellysia."
"Tell me about Southpaw."
"Tell me about Thaddeus."
"Who are Enivid's supporters?"
"Let's talk about someone else."
"Tell me about Feran."
"Tell me about The Stan."
"Tell me about Dynschall."
"Explain the election process to me."
"What kind of gossip?"
"I don't care right now."
"I just want to know where I stand in the election."
"Give me a specific breakdown of how the guilds are voting."
"I have other questions."
"The neutral guilds."
"Foresters guild."
"Mage guild."
"Landowners guild."
"Sir Becket's guilds."
"Nobles guild."
"Merchant guild."
"Thieves guild."
"Enivid's guilds."
"Thank you. Goodbye."
"Let's talk about another guild."
"Trades Guild."
"Military guild."
"Priests guild."
"Who are you exactly?"
